# kaizen secret-scan ignore list
# Gitignore-style globs (one per line). Matched paths are skipped entirely
# by the engine secret scanner (lib/quality.sh::quality_secret_scan).
# Use sparingly — prefer in-line "kaizen:allow-secret" markers on individual
# lines or replace fake values with vendor-documented examples
# (e.g. AKIAIOSFODNN7EXAMPLE) which are auto-recognised as known fakes.

# Python test/fixture files often contain placeholder credentials by design
**/test_*.py
**/*_test.py
**/conftest.py
**/tests/**
**/__tests__/**

# JS/TS test files
**/*.test.ts
**/*.test.tsx
**/*.test.js
**/*.spec.ts
**/*.spec.tsx
**/*.spec.js

# Common fixture / mock dirs
**/fixtures/**
**/__fixtures__/**
**/__mocks__/**
